Zeid bin Ra’ad said the deadly Saudi raids on Yemen show the Kingdom’s repeated failure in preventing such incidents. He said Riyadh is QUOTE- responsible for twice as many civilian casualties as all other forces put together. The attack targeting a busy market was one of the deadliest since Saudi Arabia launched its war on its impoverished neighbor almost a year ago. Saudi warplanes have been pounding Yemeni towns and cities - including residential areas- on almost daily basis. More than 8500 Yemenis, mostly civilians, have been killed so far. Millions more are facing in a dire humanitarian situation. Riyadh has defied calls by international rights bodies to end the aggression.

