Saudi Arabia Conducts Airstrikes On Shiite Houthi Rebels In Yemen. A Saudi-led coalition recently started to carrie out out air strikes against Shiite Houthi rebels in control of the Yemeni capital. 

Anti-aircraft fire erupted in response to what witnesses said were air strikes by the coalition forces against a camp at al-Istiqbal, on Sanaa\'s western entrance.

Several sunni arab countrys joined the coalition to fight the shiite houthi rebels In Yemen.

The coalition including countries from the Middle East to Pakistan were also said to be prepared to commit troops for a ground assault. This would mean another official war in the middle east.

